shared_text:
Community Free Library-Holley
August 14 at 3:06 PM ·

As you may have seen on the Orleans Hub last month, the county is installing WiFi hotspots throughout Orleans to increase internet access in our communities. The Holley Hotspot network is now up and running at the library! We've been informed that the signal at it's strongest should reach a 300 ft radius from it's location, meaning Internet can be used from this hotspot at Holley Gardens and throughout the village square, with decent signal available still outside of that. The network is open with no password. Next time you're nearby, connect to Holley Hotspot!
text:
Community Free Library-Holley
August 14 at 3:06 PM ·

As you may have seen on the Orleans Hub last month, the county is installing WiFi hotspots throughout Orleans to increase internet access in our communities. The Holley Hotspot network is now up and running at the library! We've been informed that the signal at it's strongest should reach a 300 ft radius from it's location, meaning Internet can be used from this hotspot at Holley Gardens and throughout the village square, with decent signal available still outside of that. The network is open with no password. Next time you're nearby, connect to Holley Hotspot!

shared_text:
Community Free Library-Holley
August 14 at 1:35 PM ·

So much important information that we're sharing today! Approved by our Board of Trustees on August 13th, 2020, effective immediately, we will be temporarily closed Monday nights from 4-8 pm. We will remain open Wednesday nights from 4-8 pm. Normally, we reopen on Saturdays in September, but we are delaying that until at least October. This decision was made to accommodate the needs of our staff during this time. Thank you for understanding and being patient with us!

Route is: South on Kendall Rd, left (East) on Roosevelt Hwy, left into Kendall JSHS go around bus loop to rear of building, past the tennis courts, left onto street next to Crosby's, left onto Roosevelt Hwy, left onto Countyline Rd, left on Kenmore Rd, right onto Crandall Ave, and back to Orleans Mill Works. Please practice safe social distancing, use masks, wash hands, etc. Decorate vehicles and front lawns, wave from front doors and have fun!

post_text: Information on how to obtain a public library card in the NIOGA system is below ...
shared_text:
Community Free Library-Holley
April 10 at 4:00 PM ·

To create a new library account (If you haven't had a card in the NIOGA system before), please Private Message our page or E-mail use at holpr@nioga.org with the following:
First and Last Name
Full Address
Birth date
Phone Number
E-mail (Optional)

During the week, a staff member will contact you with your new library card number. You can use your card number to access online material. When the library reopens, you can pick up your physical card to check out items in library.

post_text: WXXI helped us make the last two days full of fun and learning for our students!
shared_text:
WXXI
February 12 at 5:18 PM ·

The students, teachers, principals & staff of Kendall Central School District know how to hold a Wild Kratts Official Family Fun Day Kick-Off Assembly!! Hungry, Hungry, Hippo for the win! Students got excited for their upcoming family fun night while learning about African wildlife via the popular PBS show, Wild Kratts. The Hippo for example was a fan favorite. Activities & challenges seen below made learning extra fun!
